# React UI Rules

Use React components cleanly.

Prefer:
- Functional components
- TypeScript types for props
- Server/client component boundaries when using Next.js
- Controlled components for forms where appropriate
- Composition over inheritance
- `children` for flexible layout components
- Extracted components for repeated UI sections

When using shadcn/ui:
- Treat shadcn/ui components as owned source code.
- Customize through variants and composition.
- Do not heavily modify base components unless needed.
- Keep component APIs consistent.

When using Tailwind:
- Use `clsx`, `cn`, or a similar helper for conditional classes.
- Use class variance utilities for component variants when useful.
- Avoid deeply nested ternaries in JSX.
- Avoid unreadable className blocks.

Do not:
- Put API calls directly inside deeply nested visual components.
- Mix server data logic with presentational components.
- Create one giant page component.
